The paper deals with the parameterized version of a graph problem, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), or computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of reduction rules and kernelization techniques further supports these sub-categories.
